{{Multiple issues | Citation needed = November 7, 2015 | Wikify = November 7, 2015 }} {{Shrine | name = Tenman Tenjin-gū | religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] |image = [[File:Tenman Tenjin-gū (Ichikawa) 06.jpg|240px]] | location = {{ill|Ichikawa City|ja|市川市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Chiba Prefecture|ja|千葉県|12=draft|12=draft}}, Ōno-machi 3-1948 | Map = | deity = {{ill|Sugawara no Michizane|ja|Sugawara no Michizane|12=draft|12=draft}} | Rank = | consecration_year = {{ill|Tengyō|ja|天慶|12=draft|12=draft}} 1 ({{ill|938|ja}})|Main hall = | Alias = | Fuda-sho = | Annual festival = | Rituals =|12=draft|12=draft}}
'''Tenman Tenjin-gū''' (天満天神宮) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|12=draft|12=draft}} located on the site of the former {{ill|Ōno Castle (Shimōsa Province)|ja|大野城 (下総国)|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Ichikawa City|ja|市川市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Chiba Prefecture|ja|千葉県|12=draft|12=draft}}. The shrine is managed by {{ill|Honkōji Temple (Ichikawa)|ja|本光寺 (市川市)|12=draft|12=draft}}, a {{ill|Nichiren Buddhism|ja|Nichiren宗|12=draft|12=draft}} temple. It is also known as '''Ōno Tenman Tenjin-gū''' (大野天満天神宮).
== Origins and History ==
According to tradition, the shrine was established in {{ill|Tengyō|ja|天慶|12=draft|12=draft}} 1 ({{ill|938|ja}}) by {{ill|Taira no Masakado|ja|Taira no Masakado|1=Taira no Masakado|12=draft|12=draft}}, who enshrined the deity of the {{ill|Kitano Tenmangū|ja|北野天満宮|12=draft|12=draft}} in Kyoto at this location. A hanging scroll depicting {{ill|Sugawara no Michizane|ja|Sugawara no Michizane|12=draft|12=draft}}, which includes a record of this origin, remains preserved. It is also noted that {{ill|Nichiren|ja|Nichiren|12=draft|12=draft}} performed a dedication ceremony for the shrine. Later, Honkōji Temple became the shrine’s {{ill|bettō|ja|別当|12=draft|12=draft}} (caretaker temple), and it has remained under the temple’s management since the {{ill|Meiji era|ja|明治時代|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Honkōji Temple Historical Records ==
* In {{ill|An'ei|ja|安永|12=draft|12=draft}} 7 ({{ill|1778|ja}}), the 19th head priest of Honkōji, Kangu-in {{ill|Nichishō (Honkōji)|ja|日正|12=draft|12=draft}} (Nichishō), restored the deity {{ill|Tenman Daijizai Tenjin|ja|天満大自在天神|12=draft|12=draft}}. * From February to March of {{ill|Tenmei|ja|天明|12=draft|12=draft}} 5 ({{ill|1785|ja}}), Nichishō (Nichishō) replaced the roof of the Tenman Tenjin-gū.
== Related Articles ==
* {{ill|Ōno Castle (Shimōsa Province)|ja|大野城 (下総国)|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Ōno Tenmangū|ja|大野天満宮|12=draft|12=draft}}
