'''Tenman Tenjin-gū''' (天満天神宮) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinto shrine|qq=}} located on the site of the former {{ill|Ōno Castle (Shimōsa Province)|ja|大野城 (下総国)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōno Castle (Shimōsa Province)|qq=}} in {{ill|Ichikawa City|ja|市川市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ichikawa City|qq=}}, {{ill|Chiba Prefecture|ja|千葉県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chiba Prefecture|qq=}}. The shrine is managed by {{ill|Honkōji Temple (Ichikawa)|ja|本光寺 (市川市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Honkōji Temple (Ichikawa)|qq=}}, a {{ill|Nichiren Buddhism|ja|Nichiren宗|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nichiren Buddhism|qq=}} temple. It is also known as '''Ōno Tenman Tenjin-gū''' (大野天満天神宮).
== Origins and History ==
According to tradition, the shrine was established in {{ill|Tengyō|ja|天慶|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tengyō|qq=}} 1 ({{ill|938|ja|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/938|qq=}}) by {{ill|Taira no Masakado|ja|Taira no Masakado|1=Taira no Masakado|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taira no Masakado|13=User:Immanuelle/Taira no Masakado|qq=}}, who enshrined the deity of the {{ill|Kitano Tenmangū|ja|北野天満宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kitano Tenmangū|qq=}} in Kyoto at this location. A hanging scroll depicting {{ill|Sugawara no Michizane|ja|Sugawara no Michizane|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sugawara no Michizane|qq=}}, which includes a record of this origin, remains preserved. It is also noted that {{ill|Nichiren|ja|Nichiren|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nichiren|qq=}} performed a dedication ceremony for the shrine. Later, Honkōji Temple became the shrine’s {{ill|bettō|ja|別当|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/bettō|qq=}} (caretaker temple), and it has remained under the temple’s management since the {{ill|Meiji era|ja|明治|lt=Meiji period|1=Meiji era|2=ja|3=明治|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji era|qq=}}.
== Honkōji Temple Historical Records ==
* In {{ill|An'ei|ja|安永|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/An'ei|qq=}} 7 ({{ill|1778|ja|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1778|qq=}}), the 19th head priest of Honkōji, Kangu-in {{ill|Nichishō (Honkōji)|ja|日正|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nichishō (Honkōji)|qq=}} (Nichishō), restored the deity {{ill|Tenman Daijizai Tenjin|ja|天満大自在天神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenman Daijizai Tenjin|qq=}}. * From February to March of {{ill|Tenmei|ja|天明|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenmei|qq=}} 5 ({{ill|1785|ja|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1785|qq=}}), Nichishō (Nichishō) replaced the roof of the Tenman Tenjin-gū.
