'''Tenman Tenjin-gū''' (天満天神宮) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]] located on the site of the former {{ill|Ōno Castle (Shimōsa Province)|ja|大野城 (下総国)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōno Castle (Shimōsa Province)|qq=}} in [[:en:Ichikawa, Chiba|Ichikawa City]], [[:en:Chiba Prefecture|Chiba Prefecture]]. The shrine is managed by {{ill|Honkōji Temple (Ichikawa)|ja|本光寺 (市川市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Honkōji Temple (Ichikawa)|qq=}}, a {{ill|Nichiren Buddhism|ja|Nichiren宗|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nichiren Buddhism|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} temple. It is also known as '''Ōno Tenman Tenjin-gū''' (大野天満天神宮).
== Origins and History ==
According to tradition, the shrine was established in [[:en:Tengyō|Tengyō]] 1 ({{ill|938|ja|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/938|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) by {{ill|Taira no Masakado|ja|Taira no Masakado|1=Taira no Masakado|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taira no Masakado|13=User:Immanuelle/Taira no Masakado|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, who enshrined the deity of the [[:en:Kitano Tenmangū|Kitano Tenmangū]] in Kyoto at this location. A hanging scroll depicting {{ill|Sugawara no Michizane|ja|Sugawara no Michizane|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sugawara no Michizane|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, which includes a record of this origin, remains preserved. It is also noted that {{ill|Nichiren|ja|Nichiren|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nichiren|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} performed a dedication ceremony for the shrine. Later, Honkōji Temple became the shrine’s [[:en:Bettō|bettō]] (caretaker temple), and it has remained under the temple’s management since the [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji period]].
== Honkōji Temple Historical Records ==
* In {{ill|An'ei|ja|安永|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/An'ei|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 安永 (元号)}} 7 ({{ill|1778|ja|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1778|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}), the 19th head priest of Honkōji, Kangu-in {{ill|Nichishō (Honkōji)|ja|日正|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nichishō (Honkōji)|qq=}} (Nichishō), restored the deity [[:en:Tenjin (kami)|Tenman Daijizai Tenjin]]. * From February to March of [[:en:Tenmei|Tenmei]] 5 ({{ill|1785|ja|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1785|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}), Nichishō (Nichishō) replaced the roof of the Tenman Tenjin-gū.
